  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2003-03-18",
    "date": "2006-11-28T17:35:40Z",
    "text": "Constitutional Amendment - Declares that the first article of amendment to the U.S. Constitution shall not be construed to prohibit the: (1) recitation of the Pledge of Allegiance to the Flag, which shall be, \"I pledge allegiance to the Flag of the United States of America, and to the Republic for which it stands, one Nation under God, indivisible, with liberty and justice for all;\" nor (2) recitation or use of the national motto, which shall be, \"In God we trust.\""
  },
